<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="F4" checkit-title="Payout Annuities">
  <statement>
                <p>Natsu wants to withdraw $1,500 every month for 26 years when they retire. If Natsu's retirement account earns 3.6% interest compounded monthly, how much must they have in order to retire?
                </p>
      
      
      <p>

      </p>
      
  </statement>
    
  <answer>
            <p>
              Natsu will need <m>\frac{d(1 - (1+\frac{r}{n})^{-nt})}{(\frac{r}{n})} = \frac{1500(1 - (1 + \frac{0.036}{12})^{-12 \cdot 26})}{(\frac{0.036}{12})} = </m> $303,628.3 to retire.
            </p>
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
